author: COMSOL
description: A tubular reactor is modeled in which a reversible dissociation reaction of a species, A <-> 2B, takes place. The example accounts for the number of molecules in the gas phase increasing along the reaction path, leading to a volume expansion of the gas mixture and acceleration of the gas. Both isothermal and nonisothermal reactor conditions are investigated.
